==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Redintegrate
<hw>Re*din"te*grate</hw> <pr>(r?*d?n"t?*gr?t)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<ety>[L. <ets>redintegratus</ets>, p. p. of <ets>redintegrare</ets> to
restore; pref. <ets>red-</ets>, <ets>re-</ets>, re- +
<ets>integrare</ets> to make whole, to renew, fr. <ets>integer</ets>
whole. See <er>Integer</er>.]</ety> <def>Restored to wholeness or a
perfect state; renewed.</def> <rj><au>Bacon.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Redintegrate</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Redintegrate
<hw>Re*din"te*grate</hw> <pr>(-gr?t)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To make
whole again; a renew; to restore to integrity or soundness.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The English nation seems obliterated. What could
<qex>redintegrate</qex> us again?</q> <rj><qau>Coleridge.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Redintegration</ent>⟦br⟧
